Description: Piece of a wooden coffin; paint on plaster; traces of Hieroglyphic text. Zitman (2010, 115, 227 (II)) identifies EA47606-615 and 614 as part of the same object.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 115, 227)
